file=Engineering/rank/custom/technical-seo-execution/assets/technical-seo-checklist.md · tsc:Technical SEO Checklist — rank/technical-seo-execution=> rank diagnoses and specs; builders (mia/raj) implement through dev review + quinn gate. The claude-seo plugin deepens this when installed. SEO facts are dated (treat as a playbook) — verify high-stakes items against current Google guidance.\n · c:Crawlability=- [ ] robots.txt correct — no accidental blocks of important paths\n- [ ] Important content reachable via internal links\n- [ ] Crawl budget not wasted (faceted/infinite URL spaces controlled)\n · i:Indexability=- [ ] Correct canonical on every page (self or intended master)\n- [ ] No accidental noindex on pages that should rank (verify — staging noindex shipped live is the classic disaster)\n- [ ] Actual indexation status checked, not assumed\n · s:Sitemaps=- [ ] XML sitemap lists only indexable URLs (no redirects/noindex/404s)\n- [ ] Submitted; matches indexable reality\n · sc&:Status codes & redirects=- [ ] 200 live \· 301 permanent \· 404/410 gone — correct\n- [ ] No redirect chains or loops\n- [ ] Soft-404s fixed (no 200 on not-found)\n · r(s:Rendering (mia seam)=- [ ] Content visible to crawlers (SSR/prerender/hydration) — not an empty JS shell\n- [ ] Structured data present in rendered output (→ structured-data-geo)\n · m&c:Mobile & Core Web Vitals (shared with mia)=- [ ] Mobile-first ready\n- [ ] Core Web Vitals: LCP \· INP (not FID) \· CLS — issues → mia (shared signal)\n · p:Path=- [ ] Findings routed: mia (frontend) / raj (server) \· dev review \· quinn gate\n- [ ] High-risk change (robots/noindex/canonical) flagged as regression-map candidate\n